---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Card from '@/components/Card.astro';
import BaseLink from '@/components/BaseLink.astro';
---
<BaseLayout 
    title="Building This Site: A Learning Journey"
    description="The technical evolution of this project, from its initial setup to iterative refinements in component design and user experience."
>
    <header class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-800 dark:text-slate-100">A Living Project</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            This website is a practical case study in modern web development. This page documents its technical evolution, showcasing key architectural decisions and the process of iterative refinement for a better user experience.
        </p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-16">
        <!-- Section 1: Component Evolution -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-6 dark:text-slate-200">1. Component Evolution: From Tabs to Scrollspy</h2>
            <p class="text-center text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                The most significant refinement was moving away from a fragmented, tab-based layout to a more cohesive single-page scroll experience, inspired by the design of the "Ancient Math" page.
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                <div class="border border-red-300 dark:border-red-700 rounded-lg p-6 bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/30">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-800 dark:text-red-200">Old Method: Tabs & Accordions</h3>
                    <p class="text-red-700 dark:text-red-300 mt-2">The `f5-vpn` page originally used `<TabbedInterface>` and `<Accordion>` components. This hid content from the user, requiring extra clicks and creating a disjointed experience.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="border border-green-300 dark:border-green-700 rounded-lg p-6 bg-green-50 dark:bg-green-900/30">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-green-800 dark:text-green-200">New Method: Scrollspy & Cards</h3>
                    <p class="text-green-700 dark:text-green-300 mt-2">The page now uses a single, flowing layout. A sticky "scrollspy" header navigates the user, while content is presented in styled cards. This improves discoverability and creates a more modern UX.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Section 2: Single Source of Truth -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-6 dark:text-slate-200">2. The Power of a Single Source of Truth</h2>
            <p class="text-center text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                A core principle of this project is to centralize all navigation and repetitive content into a single, easily editable file to ensure consistency.
            </p>
            <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border dark:border-slate-700">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-2 dark:text-slate-200">The Solution: `src/data/navigation.ts`</h3>
                <p class="mb-4 text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-400">
                    This TypeScript file exports all data for the main header, footer, and homepage cards. Adding a new page is as simple as adding one line here; all components update automatically.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Section 3: Tech Stack -->
        <section>
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center mb-8 dark:text-slate-200">3. The Technology Stack</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-center">
                <Card icon="fa-brands fa-astro" title="Astro" blurb="The core of the site. Its component-based structure and 'zero JavaScript by default' approach ensures a lightning-fast user experience." href="https://astro.build" isExternal={true} />
                <Card icon="fa-brands fa-react" title="React Islands" blurb="For complex, stateful applications like the 'Ancient Math' designers, Astro seamlessly integrates React components as interactive islands." href="https://react.dev" isExternal={true} />
                <Card icon="fa-brands fa-github" title="GitHub Actions & Pages" blurb="The entire deployment process is automated. A push to the `main` branch triggers a build and deploys the static site to GitHub Pages." href="https://github.com/features/actions" isExternal={true} />
            </div>
        </section>

        <div class="text-center mt-12">
             <BaseLink 
                href="https://github.com/kairin/google-gemini-codes" 
                text="View Full Source on GitHub" 
                style="primary"
                isExternal={true}
                icon="fa-brands fa-github"
            />
        </div>
    </div>
</BaseLayout>
